sections.heading: after overruling of demurrer to indictment
sections.text: After a demurrer to an indictment has been overruled, the accused may plead not guilty, or in bar.SourceG.S.1873, c. 58, § 447, p. 822;R.S.1913, § 9091;C.S.1922, § 10116;C.S.1929, § 29-1814;R.S.1943, § 29-1815.Cross ReferencesPlea of nolo contendere, see se
